\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Aligns selected items into a structured layout for asset creation workflows.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If all selected units are on a single track, the script behaves as a standard sequential arranger:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab units are ordered by their timeline position\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab each unit is placed immediately after the previous one\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab a 500 ms gap is inserted between units\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If selected units span multiple tracks, units are grouped according to their order on each track:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab the first unit on every track starts at the same time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab each subsequent group starts after the longest unit in the previous group plus a 500 ms gap\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab if a track contains fewer units than others, the remaining tracks continue following the same grouping logic\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 REAPER item groups are treated as single units:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab all selected items sharing the same I_GROUPID are moved together\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab the unit duration is calculated from the earliest start position to the latest end position within the group\sa180\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Creates regions from selected items, grouped by time overlap across tracks.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Deletes overlapping regions and markers before creation. Names regions from the topmost parent track. Copies parent track color to created regions. Creates an outer GROUP_ region. Ensures at least three ruler lanes exist and assigns: lane 0 = parent region lane 1 = asset regions lane 2 = parent marker\par}
}

