{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Heinzenknecht Audio Reaper Tools\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A collection of ReaScripts for REAPER focused on making my life easier working in game audio.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Install ReaPack.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab In REAPER, open {\b Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack \u8594 ? Import repositories...}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Add the following repository URL:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 https://github.com/heinzenknecht/heinzenknecht-tools/raw/master/index.xml\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Synchronize packages and install the scripts you want.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Available Scripts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Align Items for Asset Creation} \u8212- Organize items for asset export workflows.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Create Regions from Selected Items} \u8212- Generate organized regions from overlapping items.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Focus View to Selected Items} \u8212- Zoom to selected items and position the edit cursor.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Propagate Item Fades} \u8212- Copy and paste fade settings between items.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Split Items and Delete Left Side} \u8212- Trim everything before the edit cursor.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Split Items and Delete Right Side} \u8212- Trim everything after the edit cursor.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Author\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Guido Heinzenknecht\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://heinzenknecht.com/\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://www.linkedin.com/in/heinzenknecht/\par}
}
